It would be great to see if the tempo timers could be logged in a DB vs in a local cookie. As a web developer we often need to clear our cookies in most or all of our browsers which renders the Tempo timer useless as we lose all time when this happens. We have been using other browsers as a workaround but we usually have to clear cache in those also. A second great feature about doing this server side is that we can adjust our timers from any of our devices whether we are in a meeting, on the road, or anywhere really. One consistent timer would be a great Tempo improvement!

